a and personalities of Christian mysticism during the Western Middle Ages. The material is primarily approached from literary, history of mentality and psychology of religion perspectives. Basic knowledge is communicated through critical analysis and is also made accessible through a glossary. Although this work clearly focuses on German mysticism, developments in other European countries are presented in a comparative manner.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMysticismzGermanyxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aMysticismzNetherlandsxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aPhilosophy, MedievalxHistory. 4aMystik, deutsche. 4aMystik, europäische. 7aRELIGION / Mysticism.2bisacsh  aMysticism, European.  aMysticism, German.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012z978311030116808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE DES MITTELALTERS ONLINEz9783110514827oZDB-23-PHM0 cprintz978311022137440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022138140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110221381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110221381/original  a978-3-11-030116-8  E-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012c2010d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014  aZDB-23-PHM